==English==

===Etymology===
Uncertain. From [[man]] (male person) or [[manual]] (by hand) or [[mangle]] (mutilate) + [[handle]]

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-manhandle.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Verb===
'''to manhandle'''

#{{nautical}},{{transitive}} To [[move]] something heavy without aid of [[lever]]s, [[pulley]]s or [[machine]]
#{{transitive}} To [[assault]] or [[beat up]] a person
#{{transitive}} To [[mishandle]]; to [[handle]] [[rough]]ly; to [[mangle]].
#:''Please try not to '''manhandle''' the box with my favorite vase.''

[[vi:manhandle]]